        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 6:48PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 648 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 10 miles east of Kim, or 31 miles west of Springfield,
moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern Baca
and southeastern Las Animas Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
